article.linkText: Fallah scores 20 in Southern Utah's 69-63 victory against Middle Tennessee
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- — Parsa Fallah scored 20 points as Southern Utah beat Middle Tennessee 69-63 on Friday night. Fallah also contributed nine rebounds for the Thunderbirds (4-8). Zion Young was 6 of 15 shooting, including 1 for 6 from 3-point range, and went 3 for 5 from the line to add 16 points. Braden Housley was 3 of 8 shooting (3 for 6 from 3-point range) to finish with 11 points, while adding three steals. Jestin Porter led the Blue Raiders (5-8) in scoring, finishing with 26 points. Justin Bufford added 12 points for Middle Tennessee. In addition, Chris Loofe finished with eight points and nine rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
